<TITLE> Genuine landless to get vested properties: Hira </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sep 25 (bdnews24.com)Land minister Rezaul Karim Hira has said around 4,45,000 acres of vested property, occupied by influential persons, will be retrieved and distributed among the genuine landless people. "The country's 4 lakh 45 thousand acres of vested property is occupied by influential persons. The government will take legal steps to retrieve those lands and distribute among the landless," he said at inaugural ceremony of Mohammadpur cluster village at Islampur in Jamalpur on Thursday afternoon. He handed over documents to 40 families in the programme. The land ministry has taken a project to provide houses among 10,600 landless families, he said. Hira reiterated his government's stance against looting and said, "Leaders and activists of the former BNP-Jamaat government had looted the state properties worth thousands of crores of taka and bought property abroad. The minister said elections to the district and upazila councils will be held next year. Deputy commissioner of Jamalpur Kamal Krishna Bhattacharya, local MP Faridul Haq Khan, project director of cluster village Hasan Imam and district AL president Mohammad Shahidullah also addressed in the programme. bdne
